  "body": "`onMouseEnter` handler is not called when mouse over an element:\n\n``` jsx\nclass Box extends React.Component {\n    constructor(props) {\n        super(props);\n        this.state = {text: \"leave\"};\n    }\n\n    render() {\n        let enter = () => this.setState({text: \"enter\"});\n        return (\n            <div onMouseEnter={enter}>{this.state.text}</div>\n        );\n    }\n}\n\nlet container = document.getElementById(\"container\");\n\nReact.render(<Box/>, container);\n```\n\nWorks in other browsers but not Chrome (stable or canary).\n\nHowever, if you render a list of divs each has a `onMouseEnter` handler, mouse enter between them works, but not from outside to one of of divs.\n",
